race.description: Bet365 Same Race Multi Mdn Plate
race.comment: The day's other 'Valley' meeting kicks off with a fascinating race. EMPIRE SONG (16) resumes after a spell of 4.5 months. Closed last campaign with a fifth over 1106m at Sale, beaten 2 lengths. Trialling well leading into this and she looks to have come on with the break. Looks to have found a good race on resumption and he can land the knockout blow.  YUUKI (10) showed good early speed and raced on the pace last start before fading to finish sixth, beaten 2.25 lengths, over 1200m at Moonee Valley. SOUTH YARRA BELLE (8) hinted that she's ready to run a big race on debut with a slick recent Flemington jumpout win. TALLINGAS IMMORTAL (9) showed good signs in her debut campaign and won a jumpout at Seymour in readiness for this. Can resume on a positive note.
